text: Remember when $FB was the favorite "talking head" value long in FANG earlier this year? They don't. "Carpet sweepers."
@realmoney The most worrisome developments in the capital markets this week include the following: * The deterioration in the high yield bond market. (The charts of $HYG and $JNK are rolling over)
* The heightened regime of volatility in the US stock market. (Investors are facing routine and unpredictable 20-40 handle moves - up AND down- in the S&P Index daily)
* More signposts that we have seen "Peak Housing." ($KBH shares fell by -15% (the steepest drop in more than three years after the homebuilder reported that new home orders were down sharply))

* The market's exposure to a Flash Clash - by virtue of the dominance of ETFs and quant strategies - was illustrated daily this week. * The continued loss of FAANG leadership and the further strength in defensive staples. (e.g. $PG just hit a new high).
* For years the market has been forgiving - but no longer. (Witness NVDA, MU, etc.) * Stocks are now selling off on good news. Enjoy the weekend.
